What a year!! Impossible to fit it all in 10 photos. I started the year off January 1 not being able to move or get out of bed or even breathe without excruciating nerve pain… I couldn’t feel anything in my right hand or forearm. After many months of chiropractor, massage, stretching and physical therapy I had a hypertensive crisis, where I couldn’t stand up, or even stay, balanced on my hands and knees… Violently vomiting, I was taken to the ER where they found a blood pressure of 175/135 and told me I was about to have a stroke… After running a million tests, and jacking me full of meds to get my blood pressure under control I was sent home to reevaluate everything in my life… Acclimating to the new meds was wild… I was out of breath, just standing up. I made a radical shift in my diet, cut out all soda and energy drinks. Lost nearly 30 pounds and had a new focus that was much less work, and much more family. Proceeded to do more traveling than I’ve ever done in my life in a single year. This year ended with some absolutely wonderful times both with the family, with my clients, and on YouTube. Also, to my pleasant surprise, the change in diet, plus getting my blood pressure under control has almost completely resolved the nerve issue in my back, suggesting it was all part of the same problem. Huge, thanks to @injectedbymandy for being by my side through this whole thing. Massive thanks to all my clients who trusted me with their music! And enormous thanks to all 100,000 subscribers! This was a challenging year, especially in the first half.. But it feels great going into 2023 with all of these issues sorted, and a massive amount of momentum. Happy new year everyone! 
.

.
.
